<p>
    <h2>What, Where and When:</h2>
</p>
<p><a id="what">
        <h3>What is "FurCoNZ"?</h3>
    </a></p>

<p>FurCoNZ is the annual camp/convention of the New Zealand Furry community, for all things that are "furry", that is
    typically held around summer each year.</p>
<p>Unlike most other furry conventions/gatherings that are held overseas, us Kiwis like to keep things simple and
    informal. Also, we like to enjoy the clean, green New Zealand outdoors and a lot of activities and events reflect
    this fact. For FurCoNZ 2009, 2010 and 2011 we arranged and offered activities such as archery, abseiling, kayaking
    and hiking for our participants.</p>
<p>For the less outdoor keen types we also have a dedicated Art Space, a gaming area and we will be screening
    Furry-related shows and movies, so there is something for everyone to enjoy while at FurCoNZ.</p>

<p><a id="furry">
        <h3>What is 'Furry'?</h3>
    </a></p>
<p>The answer to that question is rather complicated and differs from person to person. In broad terms it is people who
    are fans of Anthropomorphics. For more than that, we defer to <a href="http://whatisfurry.org">WhatIsFurry</a>.</p>

<p><a id="opento">
        <h3>Is FurCoNZ open to others who may not consider themselves 'Furry'?</h3>
    </a></p>
<p>Of course. We welcome anyone who is interested in joining in the fun, be they Furry, Brony, Otherkin, or just not
    sure. The only caveat to this is that they must comply with the 
    <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Terms">Terms and Conditions</a>. 
    Those who wish to cause trouble will not be welcome.
</p>

<p><a id="where">
        <h3>Where is the next FurCoNZ being held?</h3>
    </a></p>
<p>FurCoNZ will be held at the Forest Lakes Camping and Conference Center. The address is: 156 Forest Lakes Road, Otaki,
    NEW ZEALAND
    As the name of the site suggests, it is not a hotel typical of most overseas furry conventions/gatherings. This is a
    camp (similar to events like Camp Feral), with shared cabins, a communal dining area and shared toilet and shower
    facilities.</p>

<p><a id="when">
        <h3>When will it be held?</h3>
    </a></p>
<p>FurCoNZ will be held from Thursday 30th January to Sunday 2nd February 2020.</p>

