<p>
    <h3><a id="expenses">Why is this so expensive compared with previous FurCoNZ events?</a></h3>
</p>
<p>There are three parts to this anwswer:

<ol>
    <li>
    With the shift to a fully catered sites in 2017, the organisers endeavoured to keep ticket prices as low as
    possible while trying to offer the best experience possible. While the event was a success for the community, it did
    make a loss which was absorbed by the organisers, personally. FurCoNZ organizers do not profit from FurCoNZ. We aim
    to cover expenses, and leave a small portion remainder for a site deposit for the following event. Contrary to
    popular belief, FurCoNZ organizers and FurCoNZ Staff pay for their registrations as any other attendee (some even
    choose the sponsor options).
    </li>
    
    <li>FurCoNZ remains one of the only Furry Conventions in the world to offer accommodation and food as part of
    registration. Catering has been a significant issue in arranging past FurCoNZ events. We have relied on volunteers
    in the community to give up their weekend to cater for FurCoNZ. As FurCoNZ grows, the pressure on volunteer kitchen
    staff has grown, and it has become harder and harder to find volunteers for this. While Forest Lakes offeres
    catering, this comes at extra expense.
    </li>
    
    <li>We surveyed attendees after the previous FurCoNZ events and found that there was a significant majority that
    wanted to see an increase in the quality of accommodations. We believe that we have found a good solution to this
    with Forest Lakes, but this increase in quality also comes with a higher price. We firmly believe, however, that
    this remains significantly cheaper than the accommodation costs for a typical Hotel-based Convention.
    </li>
</ol>
<p>
    Full Event registrations must be paid in full by 16th January 2020.
</p>


