    <h2>Regarding Catering/Food:</h2>
</p>

<p>
    <h3><a id="catered">So this is a fully catered event, what are included with our meals?</a></h3>
</p>
<p>Meals are made fresh onsite by Forest Lakes. We will be providing 8 main meals in total:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Friday – Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner</li>
    <li>Saturday – Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner</li>
    <li>Sunday – Breakfast, Lunch</li>
</ul>
<p>
    Breakfast will typically be bread and toast with jams and spreads, a variety of cereals and fresh
    fruits. There will be at least one cooked Breakfast served during the Con.</p>
<p>
    Lunch will typically be a variety of sandwiches, baked cookies, fresh fruit and snack-sized chip
    packs.</p>
<p>
    Dinner will typically be centred around a different regional cuisine each night with a choice of at
    least two main dishes and a salad. A simple dessert, typically including ice-cream, will also be
    provided.
</p>
<p>
    A variety of snacks and hot drinks (tea, coffee, milo, etc.) will be available all day.</p>
<p>
    We will not be stocking or serving any other snack foods.
</p>

<p>
    <h3><a id="dietary">Can you cater for my significant allergy/specific dietary requirement?</a>
    </h3>
</p>
<p>
    Forest Lakes can cater for Vegetarian, Gluten Free or Dairy Free dietary requirements. If you
    have a dietary requirement outside of this list, please contact FurCoNZ staff directly before
    registration to discuss your catering options.
</p>


<p>
    <h3><a id="discount">Can I get a discount if I sort my own meals?</a></h3>
</p>
<p>No. FurCoNZ does not presently offer self catering options. Meals are prepared in bulk, and we
    are unable to offer discounts on unconsumed portions. You are, however, welcome to bring food
    from offsite as long as waste is disposed of. While the Waitawa Lodge and Lake Lodges do have
    kitchens, these are intended for tea/coffee making and are not intended for full meal
    preparation during our stay.
</p>

