<h2>Regarding Everything Else:</h2>

<p><a id="bring">
        <h3>What should I bring/pack to FurCoNZ?</h3>
    </a></p>
<p>Yourself. :)</p>
<p>
    You will need to bring all bedding materials that you may require (Sleeping Bag, Pillow,
    Blanket, etc). Mattresses will be provided.
</p>
<p>
    You will need to bring enough changes of clothes for the entire Con, as there are no clothes
    washing facilities on-site. Please also make allowances for warm clothing as nights may be
    cold or the weather may turn inclement.
</p>
<p>
    You will need to bring towels (we suggest more than one) and toiletries for washing and
    personal hygiene.
</p>
<p>
    You will need to bring any personal medication you may require. If you have a severe medical
    condition, bring spare medication (eg. Inhalers, Epi-pens, Insulin). These can be left with
    the First Aid Kit in the Duty Leader cabin, for quick access in case of an emergency.
</p>
<p>
You will need to bring sunglasses, a hat, and sunscreen. New Zealand Summer sun is harsh and
sunburn is a risk even on a cloudy day.
</p>
<p>
You will need a torch.
</p>
<p>
We recommend hiking boots (for those who wish to bushwalk) and swimwear/togs (we have a
swimming pool onsite and Lake Taupo is nearby).
</p>

